    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a museum-grade 2001 BMW M3 (E46) in pristine Alpine White. This example features the legendary S54B32 inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band up to an 8,000 RPM redline. Mechanically flawless, the rod bearing service has been proactively completed, and the rear subframe\u2014a critical E46 failure point\u2014has been structurally reinforced with plates to ensure longitudinal rigidity. The ZF 6-speed manual transmission offers crisp, short-throw engagement, paired with a factory-spec M-Variable limited-slip differential for optimal corner-exit traction. This vehicle retains original factory paint depth and a concours-level undercarriage, free of oxidation or fluid seepage. Every bushing, Bilstein damper, and seal remains in peak operating condition, preserving the telepathic steering response and mechanical harmony for which this chassis is renowned.",
      "price": 46900.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 44
    },
    {
